    "The Convolutional Gated Recurrent Unit (GRU) is a variant of the GRU, a type of Recurrent Neural Network.",
    "Initially, it's designed for video data, capturing spatiotemporal features by introducing convolution operations within the GRU.",
    "This results in efficient capture of local patterns and reduced computational complexity.",
    "It's used in tasks like action recognition and video captioning (93).",
    "Figure 8 displays a diagram of the suggested network, accompanied by a comprehensive schematic of a ConvGRU 620 cell."
